cell.maze.Pathfinder

Class Pathfinder

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • cell.maze.Pathfinder.Pathfinder
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Astar

    public abstract class Pathfinder
extends java.util.Observable
    An interface to be implemented by different pathfinding classes, designed for finding paths between two Cell objects in a CellGrid representation of a maze.

    • Method Detail

      • findPath

        public abstract MyArrayList findPath(Cell start,
                   Cell finish,
                   CellGrid grid,
                   int delay)
        A method that that, when implemented, should find a path between two Cell objects (start and finish) in a CellGrid representation of a maze. Note that the delay parameter is intended to be used when animating/multithreading, might be refactored and separated from this method in the future.
        Parameters:
        start - the Cell object from which to path is searched.
        finish - the Cell object ti which the path is searched.
        grid - the CellGrid representation of the maze in which the path is searched.
        delay - the delay (in ms.) used as a parameter when sleeping the thread.
        Returns:
        a MyArrayList list containing the Cell objects that are in the path
